     Understanding Poverty

   Global data and statistics, research and publications, and topics in
   poverty and development

     * image
       Millions of people still live on less than $1.90 a day, which is
       defined as extreme poverty. A number of challenges remain if we are
       to meet the World Bank’s twin goals of ending poverty and boosting
       shared prosperity.

